Overview

Using shiny app, we want to demonstrate that, means of simulated samples drawn from a given population is normally distributed, even though the original population follows distributions other than normal. In this case, we will use populations that follows exponential distribution with \(\mu = 50\) and rate parameter \(\lambda = 1/50 = 0.02\).

Simulated Sample Means Follow Normal Distribution

From the shinyApp, the means of simulated samples follows normal distribution; Gaussian curve. Also, as the sample size increases, the overall mean approximates population true mean.This demonstrates the central limit theorem that states; large number of samples will approximate the true expected values (mean) of population where the samples were drawn from.
